        "text": "Domaine is located in the town of La Londe les Maures, facing the sea. It is made up of 11 parcels spread over 22km between La Londe and Pierrefeu, each with its own exposure, climate and soil. The \"Les Fantastiques\" cuvées embody the quintessence of this diversity of terroirs, a true richness for the wine. The Château Sainte Marguerite obtained Ecocert certification in 2003, which means it is fungicide-, inSecticide- and herbicide-free. The Domaine also guarantees 100% plant-based production (no animal inputs). Les Fantastiques Rosé is the result of a blend of Grenache for aromatic intensity and silkiness, Cinsault for delicacy, and Rolle for freshness and complementary aromatic structure. The grapes, which come from the best plots, undergo cold skin maceration before pressing to preserve the intensity of the fruit. Vinification takes place in temperature-controlled vats, with ageing on fine lees.\n\nBalanced and structured, the wine is characterized by its finesse, freshness and aromas. The color is pearly pink with luminous golden highlights. The nose is intense, with rich aromas of pear and white peach, and more eXOtic nuances of lychee and passion fruit, enhanced by a zest of grapefruit. The palate is generous, silky and automatically fresh, with floral notes of rose and jasmine, greedy pear juice and lively lemon that prolongs the tasting experience.\n\nThis Côtes de Provence Rosé Château Sainte Marguerite Les Fantastiques 2023 offers great finesse and subtlety. It's the perfect accompaniment to noble seafood, such as grilled Breton lobster, but to make it \"more eXOtic\", try it with a fine Moroccan tajine of chicken, carrots, olives and preserved lemon!"
